# dependencies
library(SCED)

# dependencies required by SCED
library(broom)
library(coin)

library(bootES)
library(boot)

library(timesavers)  # from github/ianhussey

# disable scientific notation
options(scipen = 999)

Simulate two participants

# simulate data
data <- simulate_data(participants = 2,    # two participants
                      timepoints_a = 10,   # 10 timepoints pre 
                      timepoints_b = 10,   # 10 post intervention
                      cohens_d = 1) %>%  # Cohen's d = 1.5
  mutate(Participant = paste("Participant", Participant))
# analyse
results <- sced_analysis(data = data)
# sced_summary(results = results) %>%
#   kable()

results %>%
  kable()
Participant p median_difference ruscios_A ruscios_A_ci_lwr ruscios_A_ci_upr hedges_g hedges_g_ci_lwr hedges_g_ci_upr
Participant 1 0.0727 0.905 0.72 0.938 0.462 0.81 -0.11 1.74
Participant 2 0.0141 1.215 0.80 0.969 0.571 1.10 0.20 1.86 
# plot
sced_plot(data = data)

# meta analysis
meta_analysis <- sced_meta_analysis(results = results)

# forest plot
forest(meta_analysis$model_fit, 
       xlab = "Odds ratio",
       digits = 2,
       atransf = exp,
       addcred = TRUE)

Meta analysis: k = 6, Ruscio’s A = 0.911, 95% CI [0.846, 0.95], 95% CR [0.846, 0.95]

Heterogeneity tests: Q(df = 5) = 4.35, p = < .001, tau^2 = 0, I^2 = 0, H^2 = 1
